    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hi, I'm wondering, does it make any sense to allow using cross-contract constants in this manner? i.e., something akin to:\r\n\r\nA.sol:\r\n\r\n```pragma solidity ^0.4.19;\r\n\r\ncontract A {\r\n  uint public constant N = 42;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nB.sol:\r\n\r\n```pragma solidity ^0.4.19;\r\n\r\nimport './A.sol';\r\n\r\ncontract B {\r\n  uint[A.N] a;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThanks!",
